Exhibit 2 shows the racial and ethnic breakdowns for reportable offense incidents compared to
each group’s share of public school enrollment as of September 30, 2025. Of the 1,488 reported
incidents, 64% involved Black students, 16% were white, 11% were Hispanic, and almost 9%
involved students of two or more races. Asian, American Indian or Alaskan Natives, and Native
Hawaiian/Pacific Islanders accounted for less than 2% of the total.
